Adventure Deck<br />
  [1] Rohirrim Road<br />
  [2-9] take your pick    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Bid 0 and hope you have a Saved from the Fire. If you do, burn Lorien for Elrond, Cirdan, and support of the last homely house. Homely house hopefully gives you the option of moving to 3 after putting all of those beads in. If you somehow get your site 1, exert Lorien before you burn him.<br />
If you don&#39;t get Saved from the Fire, use a mulligan or cross your fingers. Isildur and Gandalf can fight, but that&#39;s about it, be careful about putting twilight in the pot if you didn&#39;t draw any backup fighters. DO NOT LET GALADRIEL DIE! Ideally Lorien and Ordullus are for burning, but if it&#39;s down to either them or someone important, don&#39;t make the wrong choice.<br />
With or without Saved from the Fire, 13 elven events make Cirdan a happy boy. If you haven&#39;t played with him yet, he gets better and better as the game goes on. <br />
There&#39;s only 1 possesion (glamdring) so don&#39;t play it vs corsairs. It also provides a little orc protection and some additional skirmish power. <br />
I found the roaming orc shadow side on dgma, I&#39;ve only played them a few times and they are pretty good.<br />
Unless you get stuck with 3 advance scouts in your opening hand, try to hold on to them until site 6 or above, that&#39;s when he really shows his worth.<br />
Other than that, just play them as you see fit. They don&#39;t take a lot of brainpower. </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
